  <front>
   <head>EPIGRAM ON SAID OCCASION,</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O Death, hadst thou but spar'd his life,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Whom we, this day, lament!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">We freely wad exchang'd the wife,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">An' a' been weel content.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ev'n as he is, cauld in his graff,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The swap we yet will do't;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tak thou the Carlin's carcase aff,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Thou'se get the saul o' boot.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
